BT /F1 10 Tf 54 639 Td (This project investigates whether GLP-1 receptor agonists \(a rapidly expanding class of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 625 Td (medications used in diabetes and weight management\) are disproportionately reported with) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 611 Td (severe gastrointestinal \(GI\) adverse events in the FDA FAERS spontaneous reporting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 597 Td (system. The central research questions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576 Td (- Do GLP-1 agents show a pharmacovigilance signal for severe GI terms \(gastroparesis,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 562 Td (pancreatitis, ileus, bowel obstruction\)?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548 Td (- Which patient phenotypes \(clusters\) and medication combinations \(Apriori rules\) are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534 Td (associated with elevated severe GI reporting?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 520 Td (- Can we predict which adverse-event reports will escalate to hospitalization or life-) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 506 Td (threatening outcomes using patient-level features?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 485 Td (Why it matters) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 471 Td (---------------) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 457 Td (Rapid uptake of GLP-1s in clinical practice requires robust post-marketing safety) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 443 Td (monitoring for serious adverse events. FAERS provides a large, public dataset of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 429 Td (spontaneous reports that can detect signals warranting further epidemiologic validation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415 Td (Findings inform clinicians, regulators, and researchers about potential high-risk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401 Td (subgroups and drug combinations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 380 Td (Data & Timeframe) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 366 Td (-----------------) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 352 Td (- FDA FAERS ASCII quarterly zip files \(DEMO, DRUG, REAC, OUTC, THER\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 338 Td (- Study window: 2023Q1 -> 2026Q1 \(13 consecutive quarters\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 324 Td (- Scripts are in Python and use `pandas`, `scikit-learn`, and `mlxtend`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 303 Td (Cohort definitions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 289 Td (------------------) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 275 Td (- GLP-1 cohort: reports containing an active ingredient that matches the curated GLP-1) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 261 Td (list \(SEMAGLUTIDE, LIRAGLUTIDE, DULAGLUTIDE, TIRZEPATIDE, EXENATIDE\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 247 Td (- Control cohort: reports containing control drugs \(METFORMIN, SITAGLIPTIN,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 233 Td (EMPAGLIFLOZIN, DAPAGLIFLOZIN, GLIPIZIDE, GLIMEPIRIDE\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 212 Td (ETL pipeline \(what & how\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 198 Td (-------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 184 Td (1\) Ingestion: read each quarterly FAERS zip; parse tables using dollar-delimited format.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 170 Td (2\) Per-quarter processing:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 156 Td (   - Normalize primaryid and caseid to string.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 142 Td (   - Deduplicate DEMO per quarter by caseid, keeping the latest caseversion/fda_dt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 128 Td (   - Tag drugs by case-insensitive substring matching on prod_ai \(active ingredient\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 114 Td (   - Filter REAC for GI Preferred Terms \(conservative curated PT list\) and mark) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 100 Td (is_gi_severe.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 86 Td (   - Parse THER.start_dt for therapy start date and compute time_to_onset_days relative) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 72 Td (to event_date.) Tj ET
endstream
